2026-03-04 13:26:02,303 807513 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'goal', 'text': "Create a `/pretty` skill that audits a DUI page for visual polish issues and fixes them. The skill takes a page ID, loads it in the browser, and systematically checks against a checklist of visual design rules — then fixes what it finds.\n\n**Not a redesign tool** — it polishes what's already there. The page must be functionally migrated first.\n\n## Visual Polish Checklist\n\n### 1. Spacing & Alignment\n- Consistent margins/padding — same spacing between like elements, no random gaps\n- Vertical rhythm — uniform row height and inter-row spacing throughout a form\n- Horizontal alignment — labels align, inputs align, columns align on a grid\n- Symmetry — equal whitespace on both sides of centered content\n- Edge alignment — elements at the same nesting level share the same left/right edge\n\n### 2. Sizing & Proportion\n- Button consistency — all buttons at the same level share the same height (and width where grouped)\n- Input width consistency — inputs in the same column are the same width\n- Label width consistency — all labels in a form column use the same fixed width\n- Icon sizing — all icons at the same level are the same pixel size\n- Touch targets — minimum clickable area (32-44px)\n\n### 3. Color & Contrast\n- Text contrast — sufficient contrast ratio against background (WCAG AA)\n- Readonly distinction — visually different from editable (dashed border, reduced opacity)\n- State colors — consistent success/warning/error/info across all components\n- Focus indication — clear visible focus ring on interactive elements\n- Hover feedback — subtle background change on hoverable elements\n\n### 4. Typography\n- Font size consistency — one size for labels, one for inputs, one for headers\n- Font weight hierarchy — bold for headings/fieldset legends, regular for labels/values\n- Text truncation — overflow ellipsis rather than wrapping or overflowing\n- Line height — consistent across all text elements\n\n### 5. Structure & Hierarchy\n- Visual grouping — related fields in fieldsets with clear boundaries\n- Consistent nesting — fieldsets within tabs within forms — same pattern everywhere\n- Section spacing — more space between groups than between items within a group\n- Tab consistency — all tabs same height, icon size, text size\n\n### 6. Borders & Dividers\n- Border consistency — same style/weight/color for all inputs at the same level\n- Fieldset borders — uniform across all fieldsets\n- Separator lines — consistent weight and color\n- Border radius — same rounding on all similar elements\n\n### 7. Responsiveness & Overflow\n- No horizontal scroll — content fits within its container\n- No micro-scroll — no tiny scrollable areas from nested overflow\n- Flex fill — panels stretch to fill available space, no dead whitespace\n- Overflow handling — scroll where needed, clip where appropriate\n\n### 8. Polish Details\n- No orphaned labels — every label has its input, every input has its label\n- No empty space — columns balanced, no large blank areas next to dense areas\n- No flash of unstyled content / layout shift on load\n- Disabled state — visually distinct, consistent opacity/cursor\n- Selection highlight — clear which row/node/tab is active\n- DUI mixin compliance — all inputs via +fitem(), all multiline via class:'textarea', no raw HTML tags"}
2026-03-04 13:26:21,660 807513 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'plan', 'text': '## Plan\n\n### Skill Structure\n- Skill file: `.claude/skills/pretty/SKILL.md`\n- Arguments: `<module/page>` (e.g. `vwltsa/sa_jobman`)\n- Optional second arg: `fix` (default is audit-only report)\n\n### Procedure\n\n#### Phase 1: Static Audit (pug source)\n1. Read the page\'s pug file + any fragment includes\n2. Check for DUI mixin compliance:\n   - Raw `input()` / `select()` / `textarea()` tags → should be `+fitem()`\n   - `+input()` calls → should be `+fitem()`\n   - `class:\'textbox\'` + `data-options:"multiline:true"` → should be `class:\'textarea\'`\n   - Inline `style=` attributes → should be in CSS file or Tailwind classes\n   - EUI class names (`easyui-*`) → should be DUI equivalents\n3. Check CSS file for hardcoded colors (hex/rgb) that should be DaisyUI vars\n\n#### Phase 2: Visual Audit (browser)\n1. Navigate to page via token URL\n2. Load data (select a record if applicable)\n3. Screenshot full page\n4. Run DOM measurements via browser_evaluate:\n   - Collect all `.fitem` bounding rects → check vertical rhythm, label widths, input widths\n   - Collect all `fieldset` margins → check section spacing consistency\n   - Collect all button dimensions → check size consistency\n   - Collect all font sizes → check typography consistency\n   - Check for overflow (scrollWidth > clientWidth)\n   - Check for micro-scroll containers\n5. Compare measurements against thresholds → flag violations\n\n#### Phase 3: Report\nGenerate structured report:\n```\n## Pretty Audit: <page>\n\n### Source Issues (pug)\n- [ ] Line X: raw input() — use +fitem()\n- [ ] Line X: multiline textbox — use class:\'textarea\'\n\n### Visual Issues (browser)\n- [ ] Spacing: .fitem rows have inconsistent margins (8px, 12px, 8px)\n- [ ] Sizing: label widths vary (120px, 140px, 120px)\n- [ ] Overflow: #panel has horizontal scroll\n\n### Score: X/10\n```\n\n#### Phase 4: Fix (if `fix` arg provided)\n- Apply pug source fixes automatically\n- CSS fixes where safe (margin normalization, var replacements)\n- Screenshot after fixes for comparison\n\n### Steps to Build\n1. Write the SKILL.md with full procedure and checklist\n2. Create DOM measurement script (reusable JS snippet for browser_evaluate)\n3. Test on sa_jobman (complex page, good coverage)\n4. Test on sa_parts (simpler page, different layout)'}
